<section class="sodium-sci">
  <div class="wrap-wide">
    <div class="ss-head">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">The sodium math</span>
        <h2>Real hydration needs <em>real</em> sodium.</h2>
      </div>
      <p>Sodium is the mineral your body actually loses when you sweat — and the one most sports drinks under-dose for taste, not performance.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ss-grid">
      <div class="ss-card is-them">
        <span class="lbl">What your body loses</span>
        <div class="big">800–1,200<small style="font-family:var(--font-mono); font-size:14px; letter-spacing:.1em; color:var(--ink-mute); display:block; margin-top:6px;">mg / hour sweating</small></div>
        <p class="desc">A single hour of intense effort can drain over a gram of sodium from your body. Heavy sweaters lose even more in heat.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ss-card is-them">
        <span class="lbl">In typical sports drinks</span>
        <div class="big">200–400<small style="font-family:var(--font-mono); font-size:14px; letter-spacing:.1em; color:var(--ink-mute); display:block; margin-top:6px;">mg per bottle</small></div>
        <p class="desc">The bestsellers under-dose sodium by 4–6× compared to what an athlete actually loses. You're chasing a deficit you can't close.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ss-card is-ours">
        <span class="pill">IONIQ</span>
        <div class="big">750<small style="font-family:var(--font-mono); font-size:14px; letter-spacing:.1em; color:var(--ink-mute); display:block; margin-top:6px;">mg per sachet</small></div>
        <p class="desc">A clinical dose calibrated to what the body actually loses — sourced from 9× fire-roasted bamboo salt, not industrial sodium chloride.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="ss-foot">"This formula is designed for real hydration. <strong>Not flavoured water.</strong>"</p>
  </div>
</section>
